/*
 * $Id: ChangeLog,v 1.3279 2004/08/05 12:30:35 mauriliolongo Exp $
 */

/* Use this format for the entry headers:
   YYYY-MM-DD HH:MM UTC[-|+]hhmm Your Full Name <your_email@address>
   For example:
   2002-12-01 23:12 UTC+0100 Foo Bar <foo.bar@foobar.org>
*/

2004-08-05 08:18 UTC-0800 Luis Krause Mantilla <lkrausem /*at*/ shaw /*dot*/ ca>
  * source/rtl/tget.prg
    ! Fixed a Clipper compatibility issure in Static Function BuildGetColor()
      when the param received was non-numeric.  
      Reported by David Arturo Macías Corona

2004-08-05 14:25 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
  * source/rtl/memoedit.prg
    ! clipper 5.2 memoedit treats a NIL as a ME_DEFAULT
    * added missing symbolic defines inside ::HandleUserKey() method.

2004-08-05 14:30 UTC+0200 Lorenzo Fiorini <lorenzo_fiorini/at/teamwork.it>
  + include/tip.ch
    * missed tip.ch header

2004-08-05 14:15 UTC+0200 Lorenzo Fiorini <lorenzo_fiorini/at/teamwork.it>
  + source/tip/*
    * copied contrib/tip/*, added copyright headers, changed file names
    * to 8.3, updated gnu Makefile ( please update other makefiles )
  + tests/tiptest/*
    * copied contrib/tip/tests, changed file names to 8.3
  * source/rtl/Makefile
    * added tip dir for HB_ARCHITECTURE <> dos
  * config/global.cf
    * added @ to for to avoid echo

2004-08-05 02:20 UTC-0800 Brian Hays <bhays@abacuslaw.com>
  * xdiff.txt
    * 2 tiny typos.

2004-08-04 19:46 UTC-0500 Vicente Guerra <vicente@guerra.com.mx>
  * source/rtl/tbrowse.prg
    * ::ForceStable() and ::Stabilize() are now "front ends" for
      ::PerformStabilization(), which receives lForceStable flag,
      instead using a "global variable" (instance).

2004-08-04 16:50 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron at xharbour.com>
  * include/hbclass.ch
    * Corrected EXTEND ... WITH DATA to use regular match marker and smart stringify

2004-08-05 01:20 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
  * config/rules.cf
    ! fixed order of flags in rule to make a .c file from a .prg one
      $(PRG_USR) needs to be after $(HB_FLAGS) or it is not possible
      to change a default flag.

2004-08-04 13:58 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron at xharbour.com>
  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
    * Corrected minor typo in last commit

2004-08-04 1:00 UTC+0100 Ath <ath at ath.doge.nl>
  * utils/hbmake/hbmake.prg
    + Added optional extra functionality in the makescript by
      implementing #DEPENDS section. This section can be filled
      (generated) from interactive mode (-ex) by selecting the
      corresponding checkbox. Recursive scanning of sourcefiles
      is also optional, and specific file-extensions can be left
      out of the scan.

2004-08-04 22:39 UTC+0200 Lorenzo Fiorini <lorenzo_fiorini/at/teamwork.it>
  * source/rtl/round.c
    * made compatible with Clipper 5.3b
  * include/hbdefs.h
    * now HB_WIN32_IO is the default. Use -DHB_WIN32_IO_OFF to
    * disable it.

2004-08-04 10:58 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron at xharbour.com>
  * source/compiler/harbour.slx
    * Revised IS_OP() macro to support all operators.
  * xdiff.txt
    * Minor corrections.

2004-08-04 16:50 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/direct.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/regex.c
  * xharbour/source/rtl/strmatch.c
  * xharbour/source/vm/memvars.c
    ! fixed memory leaks by adding regfree() for compiled regex

2004-08-04 13:40 UTC+0200 Maurilio Longo <maurilio.longo@libero.it>
  * source/rtl/tbrowse.prg
    ! fixex colpos assignment, should change ::lConfigured only if new
      colpos is out of tbrowse display area.
    * removed all duplicated code of ::forcestable() which now calls
      ::stabilize() after setting a new iVar to signal that a full
      stabilization is required. IMHO a loop while ! ::Stabilize()
      enddo is even more clear as a solution, but requires a few more
      tests.
    * cSpacePre/Last/Width and lRect are hidden iVar so I moved them
      after HIDDEN: declaration.

    /* IMHO tbrowse still has LOTS of duplicated code which should be
       removed, just think of ::dispcell() and ::dispcellnormal() which
       do the very same thing apart for a couple of ifs...
       This code duplication makes tbrowse bigger and more difficult to
       maintain.
    */

  * config/w32/global.cf
    ! for loops require a %%var to work

2004-08-03 23:15 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rtl/regex.c
    ! fixed bug I introduced with bad casting - the problem of real
      and complex solution still active.

2004-08-03 17:55 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
   ! fixed the hack with HB_CDX_CLIP_AUTOPEN - it cannot work in such
     way because it will change the locking schemes for VFP
   * COMIX and CL5.3 scheme for creating new order implemented:
      INDEX ON .. TO .. (no TAG) => overwrite any index file with given name
      INDEX ON .. TAG .. TO ..   => ads the Tag to index file
      INDEX ON .. TAG .. (no TO) => add the Tag to the structural index
     I've found that the above is intentional when I was reading COMIX
     documentation.

2004-08-03 13:20 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
   ! fixed DBOI_ORDERCOUNT again - this time I tested it,
     sorry for troubles

