2004-08-02 12:16 UTC-0800 Ron Pinkas <ron at xharbour.com>
  * include/gfx.ch
    + Added explicit #ifdef __XHARBOUR__ guard around xHarbour PP directives.

  * include/hbdefs.h
    + Added xCC support related to stdint.h

2004-08-02 20:15 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
   ! fixed DBOI_ORDERCOUNT I broke in my last commit
   + allow ORDDESTROY() to work in shared mode but in such
     case the space allocated by order is not freed for future
     reuse. Clipper 5.3 DBFCDX never frees used space used by
     tag in ORDDESTROY() xHarbour does in exclusive mode.

2004-08-02 19:00 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * xharbour/include/hbdefs.h
   ! include <stdint.h> only for GCC - other developers can make the same
     for their compilers if supported

  * xharbour/include/regex.h
  * xharbour/source/rtl/regex.c
   + added memory statistic for regular expressions
   ! fixed memory leak in regex. Each time regcomp is used then
     regree() should be called later to free compiled pcre structure.
     Because we store compiled regex as character itmes (Ron I don't
     like it - it should be IMGO GC pointer item without hits "***"
     hack) I hacked the returned pcre structure and increased the size
     of returned string adding the compiled pcre also. It's working but
     not elegant. Please test it. I'm surprised that for such long time
     knowone noticed it but regex where consuming memory each time they
     were used (regcomp)

2004-08-02 14:30 UTC+0200 Przemyslaw Czerpak (druzus/at/priv.onet.pl)
  * include/Makefile
   + added gfx.ch - Mauricio the mail I sent to you returned to me - your
     ISP doesn't accept it.
  * xharbour/include/hbdefs.h
   * include stdint.h and modified [U]INT_{MIN|MAX}* to avoid conflicts

  * xharbour/include/dbinfo.ch
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbcmd.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbf1.c
  * xharbour/source/rdd/dbfcdx/dbfcdx1.c
   + DBI_ISREADONLY and DBI_ROLLBACK added
   + ORDFOR() change online the FOR condition like in Clipper 5.3
     and COMIX (be careful and first read documentation what it
     could cause)
   + added ORDSKIPRAW(nRows) - unfiltered raw skip
   + added ORDCUSTOM( [nTag|cTag], [cBag], [lNewSet] ) return/change
     CUSTOM index flag in tag - you can make normal index custom but
     you cannot make custom index to be normal. The custom index are
     not updated automatically but only by programmer with ORDKEYADD
     and ORDKEYDEL.
   + added ORDCOUNT([cBag]) - return number of indexes in workarea or
     in cBag if given.

2004-08-01 22:10 UTC-0300 Mauricio Abre <maurifull@datafull.com>
  * bin/bld.bat
    + Automatized build for gtAlleg based programs
      Just:
           SET HB_GTALLEG=yes
           SET HB_GT_LIB=gtalleg
           bld <yourprg>
  * source/rtl/gtalleg/ssf.h
    + Hacks for cross-gt gfx code under old Allegro branches
  * include/hbapigt.h
  * source/rtl/gtnul/gtnul.c
  * source/rtl/gx.c
    + New gfxPrimitive() function
      For cross-gt, multiplatform simple gfx primitives
  * source/rtl/gtalleg/gtalleg.c
    + Handle K_SH_F1..K_SH_F12 & K_ALT_F1..K_ALT_F12 keys
    + Full gfxPrimitive() implementation
  * source/rtl/gtwvt/gtwvt.c
    + Almost full gfxPrimitive() implementation
      (only getpixel missing)
  * source/rtl/gtcgi/gtcgi.c
  * source/rtl/gtdos/gtdos.c
  * source/rtl/gtos2/gtos2.c
  * source/rtl/gtpca/gtpca.c
  * source/rtl/gtstd/gtstd.c
  * source/rtl/gtwin/gtwin.c
    + Dummy gfxPrimitive() function
      For Win/DOS non multi gt builds
  + include/gfx.ch
    + GFX_* constants for basic primitives and other stuff
    + #translates for gfx*(...) kind of functions into gfxPrimitive(GFX_*, ...)
  * tests/gtinfo.prg
    * Now the window title gradually appears/disappears
      (stress test for GTI_WINTITLE)
  + tests/gfx.prg
    + Demo for the new cross-gt, multiplatform gfx API

